channel.title: [GUI] What is the error, with my GUI?
channel.description:
Here is the error in the compiler:
Looking for JDK Compiling scripts Scripts\Sources\AutoHerbloreProTOS.java:27: cannot find symbol symbol : class AutoHerbloreLoader location: class AutoHerbloreProTOS AutoHerbloreLoader GUI; ^ Scripts\Sources\AutoHerbloreProTOS.java:259: cannot find symbol symbol : class AutoHerbloreLoader location: class AutoHerbloreProTOS GUI = new AutoHerbloreLoader(); ^ Note: Some input files use or override a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 2 errors Press any key to continue . . .
I don't quite understand what is going on. A little background on what this is, it's a script handler (much like that of PowerBot), for my server. For every skill, there is a starting script one to display the TOS (needs to be changed, to Information) that displays a paragraph so the player can understand the skill. Next, a GUI will be booted up, that basically helps the player with the skill (a guide, if you must). Anyways, I cannot seem to find the issue here. If it's obvious, and I'm just to much of an idiot to see it, rather than "flaming" the topic, simply tell me how I could have missed it. Thanks. :cool:

item.title: [GUI] What is the error, with my GUI?
item.dc:creator: @Python1 Python_
item.description:
@Python1 wrote:

[quote=“I Vain I”]Is this even server sided?

@Error; you’re calling the class ‘AutoHerbloreLoader’ but using the class ‘AutoHerbloreProTOS’

How can you not understand that? :S[/quote]

It’s a GUI loading within a class.
